cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning to manipulate objects on a real robotic platform.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a hierarchical setup for learning from demonstration.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the agent acts from raw image observations without any access to the full state information.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a method for the agent to understand the intent of the demonstrated third-person video in its context.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a controller to predict actions to achieve sub-goals.
